Yes, you can reserve without a start time.  Yes, you can change your start time.  If you do push your start time back a couple of hours, you should make sure that it's not going to inconvenience the next raid.  A good rule of thumb is to give 20 hours between start times.<br>
<br>
Why 20 hours?  For starters, a 12-14 hour repop time, so 14 hours.  Say you have people run in &amp; CR takes 3 hours.  17 Hours.  Say you have a wipeout at the beginning, and another hour is wasted.  You're up to 18 hours now.  You kill slowly for the next 2 hours.  The next raid comes in all camped out, starting on the dot, and there's at least 2-3 hours of mobs that are up.  With 20 hours, almost all of the time, the next crew will have an over half popped plane.<br>
<br>
What you can't do, is give a start time that intrudes on the next scheduled raid.  If you have to push your raid back, it's it makes it less than 20 hours, make sure it's okay with the next raider.  Also, if you post a start time that's under oh, 20 hours from the previous raid, then it's your problem if for some reason the plane isn't fully popped when you go in.<br>
